    "_comment": "schema: id (kebab-case unique), slot (feet|neck|ring|cape|pickaxe), tier (u32, 1=lowest), name (display name = the word the player types in the forge minigame), min_blacksmithing_level (u32), min_mining_level (u32; only nonzero for pickaxes), recipe { ingots: [[ingot_id, qty], ...], valu: u64 }, perks { move_speed_mult: f32 (<1 = faster, default 1.0), stamina_loss_mult: f32 (<1 = less drain, default 1.0), double_fish_chance: f32 (0..1, default 0), no_bait_consume_chance: f32 (0..1, default 0), ore_prewrite_letters: u32 (default 0), pickaxe_tier: u32 (default 0, nonzero only for pickaxes) }. recipe.valu is computed from the formula `forge_cost = total_raw_ore_value * 1.10`, where forge_cost = ingots_opportunity_cost + recipe.valu, and ingots_opportunity_cost = sum(qty * ingot_value). recipe.valu therefore = 0.10 * total_raw_ore_value - 10 * total_qty. This keeps the markup at exactly 10% over raw materials per the design spec. Cape entries are intentionally absent — capes are achievement-granted, not forged."
  },

